<li>[ ] Treating Reddit, LinkedIn, and ChatGPT traffic as the same thing</li>
<li>[ ] Not auditing the bottom 50% of content for consolidation</li>
</ul>
<p>The teams that avoid these mistakes report 2.1x higher content marketing ROI than the teams that do not, according to our internal benchmarks across 70 industries. None of these fixes require new headcount. They require better measurement.</p>
